OL,3,CSandwell Council vote Reform UK
OL,4,Cpolitician as new council leader
OL,6,FSandwell Council has officially
OL,7,Fannounced Ray Nock as its new leader,
OL,8,Ffollowing Reform UK's local election
OL,9,Fvictory earlier this month.
OL,11,FSpeaking at a meeting of Sandwell
OL,12,FBorough Council on Tuesday, Nock said:
OL,13,F"I care deeply about Sandwell, and
OL,14,Ftruly believe we have a bright future
OL,15,Fahead."
OL,17,FReform UK secured a majority after
OL,18,Ftaking 41 out of a possible 72 seats
OL,19,Fat Sandwell Council. Labour had
OL,20,Fcontrolled the authority since 1979.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G1/4
